Setup instructions:

1- Cd inside the project directory
    - `cd mdbee_task`

2- Create a python virtual environment and activate it, then install the project requirements
    - `python -m venv .venv`
    - `source .venv/bin/activate`
    - `pip install -r requirements.txt`

3- Run the application server from the command line
    - `python manage.py runserver`

4- Navigate to the main page (the first time this happens, a login page will appear). You can use any of the accounts listed at the top of this page to login
    - http://127.0.0.1:8000/books

5- View book details as well as borrower status, and lets you borrow a book (if available) or return a book you borrowed (if you are authorized)

6- To test authorization, you can follow these steps:
    - Borrow a book under a given user
    - Navigate to http://127.0.0.1:8000/accounts/login
    - Login with a different user credentials
    - Attempt to return the book with the new user. You should not be able to do that, but you can still borrow a different book
    - Go back and login with the main user. You will now be able to return the book

7- To view Borrow Records:
    - Borrow and return a couple of books under differnet users to populate the database
    - Navigate to http://127.0.0.1:8000/books/borrow_records




Additional users can be created by heading to http://127.0.0.1:8000/accounts/signup

Additional books can be added to the system (with admin credentials) at http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin